# This is a Life repo

The kernel is `./.life.core` (a single Node script, in this directory). Run it from here.

## First moves

    ./.life.core status     # what's here, what's connected, what's missing
    ./.life.core help       # all commands

`status` is the orientation command. Run it first.

## What Life is

A Life repo has `.life` files in directories that want to be agent-legible. Each `.life` file declares what the directory needs (`requires:`), what it offers (`provides:`), what commands are safe to run, and how to verify it works. The kernel resolves the graph and runs the commands.

You don't need to read the kernel source. `status`, `explain <dir>`, `check`, `index`, and `help` will tell you everything.

## When you need to do something

- Add a new directory? Create `<dir>/.life`, then `./.life.core check <dir>`
- Deploy something? `./.life.core deploy <dir>` (needs `connect cloudflare` first)
- See what governs a path? `./.life.core explain <path>`
- Regenerate `CLAUDE.md` after editing `.life` files? `./.life.core reconcile`
